DESCRIPTION:Get hyped for an upcoming visit from Dr. Johanna Fernández!\n\n
 While in Bloomington\, Dr. Fernández will engage in two events hosted by CR
 RES. The first is a conversation with PhD student Manuel Martinez Alvarenga
  at Redbud Books\, where the two will discuss the theme of "How to Make Lat
 inx History a Common Good". The conversation will begin at 7:30 on October 
 15 at Redbud Books. \n\nThe next day\, Dr. Fernández will give a talk title
 d "The Historical Roots of U.S. Fascism." This talk aims to reconstruct the
  origins of fascism within the U.S.\, presenting our present moment within 
 an historical frame. The talk will be at the IMU Oak Room on October 16 at 
 4pm. \n\nWe hope to see you there!
