DESCRIPTION:Join us for a roundtable about Martinican-born\, French writer 
 and thinker Édouard Glissant (1928-2011) on Saturday\, February 22\, from 2
  p.m. – 4 p.m.<br><br>This event represents the public-facing outcome of a 
 scaffolded series of activities that began in Spring 2022 in affiliation wi
 th IU's College's Center for Theoretical Inquiry in the Humanities: weekly 
 discussions of Édouard Glissant’s <i>Poetics of Relation</i>\, leading to a
  symposium and then a special issue of the Journal of French and Francophon
 e Philosophy: "Thinking with Glissant."<br><br>This event will feature IU s
 cholars who were contributors to "Thinking with Glissant"\, including co-ed
 itors Anke Birkenmaier (Chair and Professor\, Spanish and Portuguese) and O
 ana Panaïté (Ruth N. Halls Professor in French and Italian and Director of 
 the Center of Excellence of the French Embassy at IU).<br><br>Three scholar
 s who contributed articles will also participate: Constance M. Furey (Ruth 
 N. Halls Professor of Religious Studies)\; Edgar Illas (Professor in Spanis
 h and Portuguese)\; and Nicolas Noé (Ph.D. student in French and Francophon
 e Studies\, French and Italian).<br><br>An award-winning fiction and poetry
  writer\, Édouard Glissant is arguably the most influential Caribbean think
 er of the 20th century\, who over the course of his career developed a uniq
 ue aesthetic and philosophical lexicon that has shaped the language and per
 spectives of successive generations of theorists in poststructuralism\, pos
 tcolonialism\, and globalization. His works cover virtually all genres and 
 forms\, from lyrical poetry to scholarly studies. His ideas of Relation and
  the Chaos-World are urgently relevant for our times.
LAST-MODIFIED:20250218T145305Z
LOCATION:Redbud Books\, 408 W Kirkwood Ave\, Bloomington\, IN 47404\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Glissant Talk
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
