CREATED:20250702T191025Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for the July community play reading: "of dreamers and d
 esperados" by Júlia Cerqueira on July 18th at 7:30!\n\nAs time runs out and
  the expiration of their visas approaches\, a group of immigrants do what t
 hey must to survive their circumstances (and each other) in pursuit of the 
 American Dream – whatever that means.\n\nJÚLIA CERQUEIRA (she/they\, ela/el
 x) is a Brazilian writer\, performer\, director and Artivist whose work dra
 ws from Boal’s Theater of the Oppressed. Focused on dismantling oppressive 
 systems\, Júlia creates radical spaces for transformation\, healing\, and c
 elebration\, often exploring queer\, immigrant\, and Latinx stories through
  experimental and immersive theatrical forms.Júlia has had workshops\, prod
 uctions\, and industry readings of her work in NYC at The Tank\, The Dramat
 ist Guild Foundation\, The Chain\, Ripley Grier Studios\, Columbia Universi
 ty\, and Marymount Manhattan College\, as well as internationally in Brazil
  and Portugal. Recent achievements include her nomination as a semi-finalis
 t for the Strides Emerging Playwrights Program\, a semi-finalist for the Sh
 eNYC Off-Broadway Summer Festival\, and her work Our Heroes Are Dead being 
 longlisted for the Theater503 International Playwriting Award. Other highli
 ghts include Twinge (The Tank NYC)\, Our Heroes Are Dead (The Dramatist Gui
 ld Foundation)\, Of Dreamers and Desperados (Indiana University Bloomington
 ) and endlings (DePaul University). Aside from writing and performing\, Júl
 ia is also a fervent reader\, a David Bowie devotee\, a lover of community 
 in all forms\, and a cat mom to Monet and Frida\n\nThe Redbud Community Pla
 y Reading Series is a free monthly reading series in which community member
 s and theatre professionals share in the joy of reading plays aloud togethe
 r. These unrehearsed readings offer opportunities to appreciate plays writt
 en by local playwrights and IU alums\, and established plays we may not oth
 erwise be exposed to.
LAST-MODIFIED:20250702T191025Z
LOCATION:Redbud Books\, 408 W Kirkwood Ave\, Bloomington\, IN 47404\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Play Reading Series: Of Dreamers and Desperados by Julia Aimee Cerq
 ueira 
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
