DESCRIPTION:A talk by Nat on the Democratic Socialists of America\, France 
 Unbowed\, and building a Leftist political force for our times\n\nThe 21st 
 century has wrought world-historic changes for humanity: global capitalism\
 , mass urbanization\, and instant worldwide communication. Social movements
  of women\, workers\, and colonized peoples have changed history over the l
 ast hundred years. Yet many on the left fall into nihilism or repetition of
  the failed politics of the 20th century. In contrast\, Jean-Luc Mélenchon'
 s theory of " The Peoples' Era" has inspired the France Unbowed movement to
  become the strongest left force on the European continent. What can we lea
 rn from the counterexample of the French radical left about revolution in o
 ur time?
LAST-MODIFIED:20250818T104334Z
LOCATION:Redbud Books\, 408 W Kirkwood Ave\, Bloomington\, IN 47404\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Revolution in the 21st Century
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
