DESCRIPTION:The Creative Cafe is a monthly series inspired by three main ob
 jectives:\n\n1. A desire to have dedicated spaces to honoring new residents
  and artists through performance and dialogue.\n\n2. A place for all artist
 s within Bloomington to socialize and invent new means of collaboration and
  expression.\n\n3. Time and space of proactive community-planning and desti
 gmatized conversations around migration in a country that has seen an overw
 helming increase in xenophobia and anti-migrant sentiment.\n\nDuring this c
 reative time\, we invite you to meet someone new\, hear some amazing perfor
 mers\, and strategize ways in which we as an artistic community can priorit
 ize performers and spaces that highlight conversations and lived experience
 s of migration.
LAST-MODIFIED:20250226T205414Z
LOCATION:Redbud Books\, 408 W Kirkwood Ave\, Bloomington\, IN 47404\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Creative Cafe
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
