DESCRIPTION:Join Redbud volunteers in exploring representations of place an
 d community belonging in children’s literature\, with read-alouds highlight
 ing <i>The Sea Around Us </i>by Sophie Gilmore and <i>The Last Stop on Mark
 et Street</i> by Matt de la Peña. Following read-alouds of both works\, chi
 ldren will be invited to create a personalized map of a space that holds me
 aning\, with visual inspiration being offered from <i>My Sweet Home: Childh
 ood Stories from a Corner of the City</i> by Samina Mishra and Sherna Dastu
 r\, a work that incorporates community maps illustrated by children. <br><b
 r>This event and series were made possible through a <a href="https://www.c
 o.monroe.in.us/topic/index.php?topicid=119&structureid=64" target="_blank">
 <u>Sophia Travis Community Service grant</u></a> from the Monroe County Cou
 ncil.
LAST-MODIFIED:20250402T153712Z
LOCATION:Redbud Books\, 408 W Kirkwood Ave\, Bloomington\, IN 47404\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Family Storytime & Art Event: Place\, Community\, and Belonging in 
 Children’s Literature
