DESCRIPTION:Join Redbud volunteers in exploring the illustrative styles of 
 author-illustrator Lois Ehlert’s <i>Leaf Man\, </i>as well as botanical ill
 ustrator Gillian Harris’ <i>Wake Up\, Woods</i> (authored by Michael A. Hom
 oya and Shane Gibson). Following read-alouds of both works\, children will 
 be invited to engage in activities inspired by the literature: a nature wal
 k to cultivate deeper appreciation for that which is represented in <i>Wake
  Up\, Woods</i>\, or time to create cyanotype-style sun prints\, inspired b
 y Ehlert’s collage-like illustrations in <i>Leaf Man</i>.<br><br>This event
  and series were made possible through a <a href="https://www.co.monroe.in.
 us/topic/index.php?topicid=119&amp\;structureid=64"><u>Sophia Travis Commun
 ity Service grant</u></a> from the Monroe County Council.
