UID:01tmeoasm3coj8hahi2pbdlaif@google.com
CREATED:20250528T204505Z
DESCRIPTION:What is to be done at this moment of emergent fascism and ongoi
 ng genocide?  How can we resist effectively?  Daniel Segal leads a communit
 y discussion of these questions\, using his zine\, "It's Not Going To Resis
 t Itself" (available at Redbud or via link: <a href="https://pzacad.pitzer.
 edu/~dsegal/).">https://pzacad.pitzer.edu/~dsegal/).</a>  Daniel Segal orga
 nizes with Jewish Voice for Peace and TIAA-Divest! and previously led the A
 AUP chapter at the Claremont Colleges.  He is a historian and anthropologis
 t who has worked in Trinidad and in Indigenous territory in the northern Am
 azon.   With a Palestinian comrade\, in May of 2023 he co-led a study tour 
 for US faculty and students to the West Bank.  Participants are encouraged 
 to obtain and read the zine before attending (it is very short!) but the di
 scussion will be inclusive of those who have not read the zine.  Refreshmen
 ts will be provided and please RSVP here."
LAST-MODIFIED:20250619T002251Z
LOCATION:Redbud Books\, 408 W Kirkwood Ave\, Bloomington\, IN 47404\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY: "It's Not Going To Resist Itself" - Zine discussion abt resisting 
 facism today w/ Daniel Segal of JVP
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
