CREATED:20250924T170213Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><b>Working Class Writers Tour</b></p><p>Join us for the <b>W
 orking Class Writers Tour</b>\, an inspiring event featuring a diverse line
 up of accomplished authors and poets whose work is shaped by their experien
 ces\, labor\, and unique perspectives.</p><p>This special evening will feat
 ure readings and conversation with:</p><ul><li><p><b>Angela Jackson-Brown\,
 </b> an award-winning novelist\, poet\, and playwright\, and Associate Prof
 essor at Indiana University and Spalding University. Her novels include <i>
 When Stars Rain Down</i> and the recently published <i>Homeward</i>.</p></l
 i><li><p><b>janan alexandra\,</b> a peripatetic poet\, educator\, and lifel
 ong worker who has taught in carceral spaces\, tied oyster nets\, and built
  furniture\, among other labors. Her debut poetry collection\, <i>COME FROM
 </i>\, is forthcoming in Spring 2025.</p></li><li><p><b>James Stewart III\,
 </b> a Black writer\, arts organizer from Chicago\, and co-founder of the E
 xhibit B reading series. His debut novel\, <i>Defiant Acts</i>\, is one of 
 Chicago Magazine’s “Summer’s Required Reading” picks for 2025.</p></li><li>
 <p><b>Dan "Sully" Sullivan\,</b> a poet and educator based in Bloomington\,
  Indiana\, known for his performances and workshops that explore masculinit
 y\, vulnerability\, and resilience.</p></li></ul><p>Don't miss this opportu
 nity to hear powerful voices on work\, life\, and the creative spirit. A Q&
 amp\;A and book signing will follow the reading.</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250924T170213Z
LOCATION:Redbud Books\, 408 W Kirkwood Ave\, Bloomington\, IN 47404\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Working Class Writers Tour
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
