DESCRIPTION:<p>Join us for a <strong>Skill in Action</strong> book talk and
  yoga practice at Redbud Books on <strong>Sunday\, June 22\, from 10 AM – 1
 2 PM</strong>! This gathering will include a <strong>discussion</strong> on
  <em>Skill in Action</em> by Michelle C. Johnson\, followed by a <strong>gu
 ided yoga practice</strong>. Together\, we’ll explore the intersections of 
 <strong>yoga and social justice</strong> in a welcoming community space.</p
 ><p>Can’t join in person? <strong>We’ll also offer a virtual option via Zoo
 m for the discussion and yoga practice.</strong> A link will be sent to reg
 istered participants before the event.</p><p>This is a p<strong>ay-what-you
 -can</strong> event\, with a suggested sliding scale to help support the yo
 ga instructors and Redbud Books\, a volunteer-run independent bookstore. Yo
 ur contribution supports the facilitation of this gathering\, but <strong>d
 oes not include the cost of the book.</strong></p><p>📚 <strong>Books are a
 vailable for purchase separately at Redbud Books.</strong></p><ul><li><stro
 ng>$15 – Supported Rate</strong> (for those who need financial flexibility)
 </li><li><strong>$25 – Standard Rate</strong> (covers the cost of the event
 )</li><li><strong>$40+ – Community Supporter Rate</strong> (for those who c
 an contribute more and help sustain accessible community programming)</li><
 li><strong>Pay what you can</strong> – No one will be turned away for lack 
 of funds.</li></ul><p>Payments can be made in cash at the event or via <b><
 a href="https://venmo.com/u/Cooper-Carrie-S" target="_blank">Venmo</a>.</b>
 </p><p>Your presence is what matters most—we look forward to sharing this s
 pace with you! </p><p>Register <b><a href="https://forms.gle/UCXnkec1cuCXBn
 E78" target="_blank">HERE</a> </b>to save your spot and let us know how man
 y folks to plan for.</p><p>For more details\, check out the <strong><a href
 ="https://static1.squarespace.com/static/5e5ea31c1eda104caa01e1c6/t/61783f7
 e6065102286ae0e68/1635270527647/Skill+in+Action+Book+Club+Guide.pdf" target
 ="_blank">Skill in Action Book Club Guide</a></strong> and learn more about
  the book <strong><a href="https://www.skill-in-action.com/the-book" target
 ="_blank">HERE</a>.</strong></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250619T002251Z
LOCATION:Redbud Books\, 408 W Kirkwood Ave\, Bloomington\, IN 47404\, USA
SEQUENCE:2
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Skill in Action Reading Group
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
