DESCRIPTION:<em>Storming Bedlam</em> is a radical rereading of the history\
 , theory\, and practice of psychiatry that emphasizes the utopian origins o
 f the psychiatric revolution and its roots in the political and economic re
 volutions of the 18th and 19th centuries.<br><br>The Redbud Nonfiction Read
 ing Group is a monthly reading group that actively seeks and explores books
  that expand horizons and consider new ways of thinking. Meetings generally
  happen near the end of the month\, on a Sunday\, and discussion is centere
 d around the entire text. All are welcome to attend\, regardless of reading
  progress\, in a casual environment fostering dialogue and the exchange of 
 ideas. If you have a book you would like to suggest and read\, or if you wo
 uld like to facilitate a future group\, please feel free to reach out to us
  at <a href="mailto:contact@redbudbooks.org" target="_blank"><u>contact@red
 budbooks.org</u></a>.
LAST-MODIFIED:20250401T000440Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Nonfiction Reading Group: Storming Bedlam
TRANSP:OPAQUE
