CREATED:20250702T191106Z
DESCRIPTION:"The Young Girls of Rochefort" unfolds in the charming coastal 
 town of Rochefort\, where twin sisters Delphine and Solange\, a dance and m
 usic teacher respectively\, dream of escaping their humdrum lives and findi
 ng true love. As a lively traveling fair arrives\, the town becomes a stage
  for romantic entanglements and missed connections. Delphine and Solange\, 
 each longing for their ideal partners\, find their desires intertwined with
  the romantic pursuits of other townspeople\, including Maxence\, a sailor 
 and painter searching for his perfect woman\, and their mother Yvonne\, who
  runs a local cafe. The film dances through a weekend of colorful musical n
 umbers and vibrant set designs\, illustrating the whimsical yet poignant se
 arch for love and fulfillment. Through a series of chance encounters and ne
 ar misses\, the characters navigate the complexities of romance\, highlight
 ing themes of fate\, destiny\, and the pursuit of dreams\, all wrapped in a
  lighthearted\, optimistic\, and visually captivating cinematic experience.
    \n\nOur secret screening series brings together an eclectic assortment o
 f films chosen by the film programming team based on their own interests an
 d desires.
LAST-MODIFIED:20250718T201745Z
LOCATION:Redbud Books\, 408 W Kirkwood Ave\, Bloomington\, IN 47404\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:POSTPONED Secret Screening: The Young Girls of Rochefort
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
