CREATED:20260226T185517Z
DESCRIPTION:Please join us for the next play reading on March 28th at 7 PM:
  THE DEAD PETS CLUB by local playwright Brennen Edwards!\n\nMilkshake is mi
 ssing. To her surprise\, Claire is joined by three do-gooder retirees to he
 lp search the neighborhood for her beloved cat. The Dead Pets Club embarks 
 on a winding path that leads to Baba Yaga’s front door (please\, call her B
 abette)\, and a journey of sex\, love\, friendship and change. \n\n(No anim
 als harmed in this new comedy.)\n\nBrennen Edwards is a southern Indiana pl
 aywright living in Bloomington. Their first comedy\, COFFEE BREAK (written 
 about her snarky tenure as a Starbucks barista) had a sold out weekend in t
 he Firebay Theater in 2018. COYOTES (about a disastrous family dinner durin
 g a snow storm) had a play reading at the BPP in 2019. Since then they’ve k
 ept writing\, favoring dark comedy with ping-pong dialogue and midwestern s
 ettings. Her latest\, SUPER TRAP 3000 (about the hunt for a raccoon living 
 in the walls of a community college) was a part of the Redbud Books communi
 ty play reading series in 2025. Special thanks to Annalise Cain. You can fi
 nd them and more of their work on New Play Exchange.\n\nThe Redbud Communit
 y Play Reading Series is a free monthly reading series in which community m
 embers and theatre professionals share in the joy of reading plays aloud to
 gether.\n\nThese unrehearsed readings offer opportunities to appreciate pla
 ys written by local playwrights and IU alums\, and established plays we may
  not otherwise be exposed to.
LAST-MODIFIED:20260312T160013Z
LOCATION:Redbud Books\, 408 W Kirkwood Ave\, Bloomington\, IN 47404\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Play Reading: The Dead Pets Club by Brennen Edwards
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
