RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20251107T180000
CREATED:20250927T000155Z
DESCRIPTION:<h2><span>What does anti-imperial working class internationalis
 m mean today?</span></h2><p>This talk examines the prospects and challenges
  facing contemporary anti-imperialist working-class struggle in North Ameri
 ca today. Drawing on ten years of scholarship and organizing in and around 
 the logistics sector — through port blockades in the Palestinian solidarity
  movement and through organizing with independent union of Amazon warehouse
  workers — this talk suggests that contemporary "internationalist" thinking
  remains too wedded to immaterial goals of "consciousness-raising" insuffic
 iently attentive to the concrete challenges of rooting internationalism in 
 grassroots working class movements. I re-examine two key concepts: "Interna
 tionalism" and "Class" through the work of Lenin and the Italian Autonomist
 s in order to map three methodological orientations to internationalist org
 anizing in the post-industrial imperial core: concretization\, (re)composit
 ion\, and cadrefication. By asking how internationalist struggle has been s
 haped by political economic transformations in the structure of the transna
 tional production and distribution\, I suggest ways in which organizing wit
 hin and across supply chains has produced core strategies for building work
 ing class internationalism in a logistical age.</p><h3>Charmaine Chua</h3><
 p>Charmaine Chua is a Singaporean communist. She is co-founder of the Marxi
 st Institute of Research\, teaches in the geography department at UC Berkel
 ey\, and organizes with Workers in Palestine and the Communist Caucus of th
 e DSA.</p><p><u>Suggested Readings</u></p><ul><li>Charmaine Chua\, <a href=
 "https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fi/t5qr3uqh1zqr7u5o25t62/Chapter-6-Working-Cla
 ss-Internationalism___May-13.pdf?rlkey=htpvmdrtikctfcw67ays9matj&st=cjwyb3d
 6&dl=0" target="_blank"><u>What does Working Class Internationalism mean to
 day?</u></a></li><li>Rodrigo Nunes\,<a href="https://www.versobooks.com/blo
 gs/news/3478-it-takes-organizers-to-make-a-revolution?srsltid=AfmBOoq44tHJh
 xgzkyTnfNvRrrrdaGO-fX0XS0zEF7i7GNpxjkuVTsdV" target="_blank"><u> </u></a><a
  href="https://viewpointmag.com/2017/11/09/takes-organizers-make-revolution
 /" target="_blank"><u>It Takes Organizers to Make a Revolutio</u></a><a hre
 f="https://viewpointmag.com/2017/11/09/takes-organizers-make-revolution/" t
 arget="_blank"><u>n</u></a></li><li>Salar Mohandesi\, <a href="https://view
 pointmag.com/2018/02/01/the-specificity-of-imperialism/" target="_blank"><u
 >The Specificity of Imperialism</u></a></li><li>Ruth Wilson Gilmore\, <a hr
 ef="https://api.pageplace.de/preview/DT0400.9781804292723_A48142077/preview
 -9781804292723_A48142077.epub" target="_blank"><u>Forward to Lenin\, <em>Im
 perialism and the National Question</em></u></a></li></ul><br>All readings 
 can be found on our <a href="https://rosabloom.org/year-2/"><u>Proton Drive
 </u></a>.<br>Virtual meeting link: <a href="https://us06web.zoom.us/j/86916
 851312" target="_blank"><u><u>https://us06web.zoom.us/j/86916851312</u></u>
 </a>
LAST-MODIFIED:20251017T232259Z
LOCATION:Redbud Books\, 408 W Kirkwood Ave\, Bloomington\, IN 47404\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:ROSA Bloomington | Year 2 - Lecture
TRANSP:OPAQUE
