  by Margaret Wise Brown. In addition\, poems made in collaboration with chi
 ldren in <i>My Sweet Home: Childhood Stories from a Corner of the City\,</i
 > written by Samina Mishra and Sherna Dastur\, will be explored. Afterwards
 \, participants will be invited to write or dictate a poem\, story\, or son
 g\, with offered inspiration from how the children in <i>The Dead Bird</i> 
 express their collective emotions during a bird’s funeral through song and 
 ritual. <br><br>This event and series were made possible through a <a href=
 "https://www.co.monroe.in.us/topic/index.php?topicid=119&structureid=64" ta
 rget="_blank"><u>Sophia Travis Community Service grant</u></a> from the Mon
 roe County Council.
LAST-MODIFIED:20250416T121859Z
LOCATION:Redbud Books\, 408 W Kirkwood Ave\, Bloomington\, IN 47404\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Place\, Community\, and Belonging in Children’s Literature
TRANSP:OPAQUE
