DESCRIPTION:Interested in making and sharing art that centers experiences o
 f migration?\n\nWe will have an open mic\, arts activities\, and a circle t
 alk focused on themes of migration in Bloomington. Feel free to bring somet
 hing to perform or simply join us for a creative and social moment together
 ! There will be light snacks provided.\n\n---\nThe Creative Cafe is a regul
 ar series inspired by three main objectives:\n\n1. A desire to have dedicat
 ed spaces to honoring new residents and artists through performance and dia
 logue.\n\n2. A place for all artists within Bloomington to socialize and in
 vent new means of collaboration and expression.\n\n3. Time and space of pro
 active community-planning and destigmatized conversations around migration 
 in a country that has seen an overwhelming increase in xenophobia and anti-
 migrant sentiment.\n\nDuring this creative time\, we invite you to meet som
 eone new\, hear some amazing performers\, and strategize ways in which we a
 s an artistic community can prioritize performers and spaces that highlight
