DESCRIPTION:Postponed until next week! Stay tuned for a new date for this r
 eading group.\n\nSuzuki\, who is often compared to Ursula K. LeGuin\, wrote
  sci-fi stories set within Japan’s postwar counterculture. This collection 
 of short stories is a great introduction to her work!\n\nThe Redbud Fiction
  Reading Group is a monthly reading group focusing on exciting recent liter
 ature that you might not have an opportunity to read or discuss otherwise. 
 Meetings generally happen near the end of the month\, on a Sunday\, and dis
 cussion is centered around the entire text. All are welcome to attend\, reg
 ardless of reading progress\, and the vibe is always fun and casual. If you
  have a book you would like to suggest and read\, or if you would like to f
 acilitate a future group\, please feel free to reach out to us at contact@r
 edbudbooks.org.
