DESCRIPTION:An evening of 3 performances by local musicians.\n\nOpening set
 s provided by Richard Jermain (The City Underground) and Indianapolis-based
  composer and experimental instrument designer Rob Funkhouser\; and headlin
 ing set by Water is the Sun.\n\nWater is the Sun melds the minds of Adam Pa
 rks (Timber Rattle\, Lightning White Bison) and Mkl Anderson (Drekka\, love
 sliescrushing)\, precipitating a melodic\, funereal psyche-pastoral that is
  as informed by the angelic harmonies of West Coast cults and Appalachian h
 ymns as it is by the dark new age and ambient resonance of the experimental
  scene that has embraced and supported both musicians for many years. This 
 event will be their Bloomington stop on a 2025 tour across the midwest and 
 northeast.
LAST-MODIFIED:20250330T021306Z
LOCATION:Redbud Books\, 408 W Kirkwood Ave\, Bloomington\, IN 47404\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Richard Jermain\, Rob Funkhouser\, Water is the Sun
TRANSP:OPAQUE
