CREATED:20250108T034223Z
DESCRIPTION:Why do we lose continuity in our movements from one generation 
 to the next?<br><br>Join author Peter Gelderloos in a discussion of his rec
 ent books <i>They Will Beat the Memory Out of Us</i> and <i>Organization\, 
 Continuity\, Community</i>.<br><br>With books explore the loss of collectiv
 e memory\, the lack of intergenerational continuity\, and the constant rupt
 ures in our movements that cause us to repeat the same strategic mistakes o
 r to succumb to repression\, exhaustion\, and hopelessness\, rather than bu
 ilding off our cumulative knowledge\, wisdom\, and strength.<br><br>Copies 
 of <i>They Will Beat the Memory Out of Us</i> available for purchase at the
  store!
LAST-MODIFIED:20250218T145223Z
LOCATION:Redbud Books\, 408 W Kirkwood Ave\, Bloomington\, IN 47404\, USA
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Peter Gelderloos Author Talk
TRANSP:OPAQUE
