DESCRIPTION:<br>Interested in making and sharing art that centers experienc
 es of migration?<br><br><b>April 12th at 1pm is the next Creative Cafe at R
 edbud Books.</b> We will have an open mic\, arts activities\, and a circle 
 talk focused on themes of migration in Bloomington. Feel free to bring some
 thing to perform or simply join us for a creative and social moment togethe
 r! There will be light snacks provided.<br><br>---<br>The Creative Cafe is 
 a monthly series inspired by three main objectives:<br><br>1. A desire to h
 ave dedicated spaces to honoring new residents and artists through performa
 nce and dialogue.<br><br>2. A place for all artists within Bloomington to s
 ocialize and invent new means of collaboration and expression.<br><br>3. Ti
 me and space of proactive community-planning and destigmatized conversation
 s around migration in a country that has seen an overwhelming increase in x
 enophobia and anti-migrant sentiment.<br><br>During this creative time\, we
  invite you to meet someone new\, hear some amazing performers\, and strate
 gize ways in which we as an artistic community can prioritize performers an
 d spaces that highlight conversations and lived experiences of migration.
LAST-MODIFIED:20250313T163746Z
LOCATION:Redbud Books\, 408 W Kirkwood Ave\, Bloomington\, IN 47404\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Creative Cafe
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
