DESCRIPTION:Ira\, author of Panic Now? (U of Tenn Press)\, will lead partic
 ipants to consider what we can do when our apparatus for sensemaking is col
 lapsing. How do we design practices that offset or undo collective epistemi
 c collapse? How we stay with the difficult emotions when we are experiencin
 g breakdown of processes and distance crises? This workshop will be designe
 d to support organizers\, activists\, and anyone hoping to salvage meaning 
 from our current wreckage.
LAST-MODIFIED:20260329T203507Z
LOCATION:Redbud Books\, 408 W Kirkwood Ave\, Bloomington\, IN 47404\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Panic Wisely: A workshop with Ira J Allen
TRANSP:OPAQUE
