DESCRIPTION:<i>Bye Bye Love</i> (1974) is a Japanese road movie directed by
  Isao Fujisawa that follows a young man and a gender-fluid person on a wild
 \, unconventional journey across Japan. This recently rediscovered and rest
 ored film explores themes of identity\, love\, and freedom\, while defying 
 social norms and expectations.  <br><br><i>Queer Underground</i> delves int
 o the experimental\, avant-garde\, and forgotten works of queer filmmakers\
 , showcasing the diverse and often radical expressions of LGBTQ+ identity t
 hat have pushed boundaries and challenged conventions.
