DESCRIPTION:Join us on Wednesday June 25<sup>th</sup> at 5pm for a discussi
 on of Talia Mae Bettcher's <i>Beyond Personhood: An Essay in Trans Philosop
 hy</i>. Dr. Bettcher will be joining us on Zoom! <br><br>We'll focus on Par
 t I\, "The Central Concepts: 'Worlds' Apart" (~80 pages)\, but discussion o
 f the book as a whole is welcome.<br><br>"<i>Beyond Personhood</i> provides
  an entirely new philosophical approach to trans experience\, trans oppress
 ion\, gender dysphoria\, and the relationship between gender and identity. 
 [...] Undergirding this account is Bettcher’s groundbreaking theory of inte
 rpersonal spatiality—a theory of intimacy and distance that requires reject
 ion of the philosophical concepts of person\, self\, and subject. She argue
 s that only interpersonal spatiality theory can successfully explain trans 
 oppression and gender dysphoria\, thus creating new possibilities for think
 ing about connection and relatedness." -<i>University of Minnesota Press</i
 ><br><i><br></i><br>For more overview of the book: <br>Author interview wit
 h Judith Butler: <a href="https://youtu.be/H1B4yJRV9xQ?si=MMcX7ZAmh8MP70kn"
  target="_blank">https://youtu.be/H1B4yJRV9xQ?<wbr />si=MMcX7ZAmh8MP70kn</a
 ><br><br>Dr. Bettcher on the podcast <i>Gender Reveal: <a href="https://gen
 der.libsyn.com/episode-184-talia-mae-bettcher" target="_blank">https://gend
 er.libsyn.com/<wbr />episode-184-talia-mae-bettcher</a></i>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250606T161103Z
LOCATION:Redbud Books
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Reading Group: Beyond Personhood: An Essay in Trans Philosophy
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
