DESCRIPTION:The Stop Cop City Imaginary Crimes Tour is coming to Bloomingto
 n! This international tour\, with over 70 stops\, will create dialogue abou
 t repression and resilience. Come join the conversation at Redbud books Apr
 il 11th at 7pm<br><br>The fight to Stop Cop City in Atlanta\, GA is a local
 ized iteration of the global struggle against carceral futures and a fascis
 t police state.  The trial of the RICO 61 has the potential to set legal pr
 ecedence that will ricochet throughout our movements and affect our work fo
 r years to come.  We know that the scale of repression leveled by the state
  is an indicator of the success of our movements and that from the forest t
 o the courts\, the frontlines are everywhere. Repression intends to demobil
 ize us\; anti-repression is what enables us to continue!<br><br>Stay update
 d here:<br><a href="www.instagram.com/sccimaginarycrimestour/">www.instagra
 m.com/sccimaginarycrimestour/</a><br><br>List of tour dates:<br><a href="ht
 tps://cryptpad.fr/pad/#/2/pad/view/g6H3S1Zum45tRJPwAP9t--jD2CyBQFq-rY5g6YOQ
 B8A/">https://cryptpad.fr/pad/#/2/pad/view/g6H3S1Zum45tRJPwAP9t--jD2CyBQFq-
 rY5g6YOQB8A/</a><br><br>Fundraisers and more info:<br>linktr.ee/sccimaginar
 ycrimestour
LAST-MODIFIED:20250331T165839Z
LOCATION:Redbud Books\, 408 W Kirkwood Ave\, Bloomington\, IN 47404\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Stop Cop City Imaginary Crimes Tour
TRANSP:OPAQUE
